<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5315887>
    dc:description "Fig.3. Anaballetus chilensis gen. & sp. nov., male paratype.A – meso- and metathorax in ventral view; B – prothorax and anterior leg; C–D – detail of median part of meso- and metaventrite (C – ventral view; D – ventrolateral view); E – protarsus; F – mesothoracic leg; G – mesotarsus; H – metathoracic leg and abdomen.Not to scale.Abbreviations: msvc – mesoventral carina; prre – procoxal rests; trgr – tarsal groove of protibia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5315887/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

